fields.scenario_text: There is blood on the sofa, and smell emanating from the cupboard.
The dog kept staring at the door. Why?
He pulled into the driveway, and saw the main door wide open.
Robert was getting bored sitting at his desk. It had been a quiet day at the station. His phone rang.

fields.input_text: She looked at her hands, and went to the bathroom.
There is a slight movement at the window frame. He looks to see eyes, stone cold, staring at him.
The door had been locked for the last 5 years, and she did not have the key.
He rushed into the house, afraid that something was wrong.
He thought she had left it open by mistake, and went in calling her name.
Before he could go in, she came running out, screaming loudly.
'This is my chance', he thought, as he went in quietly.
'HELP!' was all he heard before the line cut.
It was his wife, calling to say she would be late from work.
He was waiting for his master.

fields.story_text:
It was a cold day, and he sat there like he did every evening. 
Suddenly, he heard a loud scream from somewhere in the forest nearby.
A woman's scream. Getting up, he started heading toward the source of the scream.
He started seeing footsteps in the snow. But the footsteps were not those of a woman's, judging by the print, but that of a seemingly large man with large feet. (Atleast that is what he thought from the footprints.)
He started following the steps...

It was an unusually cold night. But what was even more unusual was the presence of a hooded figure on the park bench, in this snow.
He seemed to be doing nothing. He just sat there like a mannequin.
Suddenly, as if right on cue, he got up and started going down the road..

It was a cold day, and he sat there like he did every evening. 
Suddenly, he head a noise from far away. Curious, he got up and headed toward the source of the sound.

The phone rings!
On a still, cold, ghastly night!
A beautiful woman picks up the phone at the dreaded hour!
Suddenly things escalate and the woman is asking for divorce!
The husband is wondering what the <hell> is going on?
This continues till the morning(yea, its sunrise , not sunset).
In the morning, everybody is ( somehow ) exercising, happy, dancing and singing....but ( yea, obviously, we cant have a happy ending ) someone(anybody, yea, any ducking body ) comes in and shots them.!

The end!

John is swinging in a park. His sister, Mary, on the other hand is enjoying a delicious scoop of choco-chipped vanilla ice-cream. Their elder sister, Tanya is practising ballet in the community hall of the park.
There is a cave near the river side of Dholakpur which is known to be 1000 years old.

It was English Lit. It was still 45 minutes for the class to end. It was then that I noticed her. Across the second row, playing with her hair; her dark, brown luxurious  hair. I passed her my copy asking for her number.

fields.text: Snow falling. It's almost dark. A lonely man is sitting on a park bench.
Amidst the graveyard silence, the phone began to ring. A loud-clear sound..

A normal day. A normal class. It was English Literature. The Prof was going on and on about the consequences of Antony's manipulative speech after Caesar's death; how it instigated the mob and how cleverly it was done. It was stifling inside the closed room...
Richard was whistling to himself. Again no one asked him to play.
A child is swinging in a park. It's going to be dusk soon.
